# 📋 Quick Setup Guide:
#
# 1. 📁 Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. 🔥 Create Firebase Project:
#    - Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
#    - Click "Create a project" or select existing project
#    - Follow the setup wizard
#
# 3. 🔐 Enable Authentication:
#    - In Firebase Console, go to Authentication > Sign-in method
#    - Enable "Email/Password" provider
#    - Enable "Google" provider
#    - In "Authorized domains", add:
#      * localhost (for development)
#      * your-domain.com (for production)
#
# 4. ⚙️ Get Configuration:
#    - Go to Project Settings (gear icon) > General
#    - Scroll to "Your apps" section
#    - Click "Web app" or add new web app
#    - Copy the config values to your .env file
#
# 5. 🔄 Restart Development Server:
#    - Stop your dev server (Ctrl+C)
#    - Run: npm run dev
#
# 🐛 Troubleshooting:
#
# ❌ "Firebase configuration error":
#    → Check all VITE_FIREBASE_* variables are set in .env
#    → Ensure no placeholder values remain
#    → Restart dev server after .env changes
#
# ❌ "Google sign-in not enabled":
#    → Enable Google provider in Firebase Console
#    → Check Authentication > Sign-in method
#
# ❌ "Unauthorized domain":
#    → Add your domain to Firebase authorized domains
#    → Include localhost for development
#
# ❌ Still having issues?
#    → Check browser console for detailed errors
#    → Verify .env file is in project root
#    → Ensure .env is not in .gitignore
